.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-ASSIST 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-assist \- AI producer: capture context, triage, and author or drive a playbook
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR assist [<prompt>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
assist captures the bounded origin context (last command, exit code, scrollback,
cwd/project root), triages the request, and either types a suggested command
back into your shell, renders a short prose answer, or authors and drives a
full playbook. With no <prompt>, it prompts interactively (a float under a
multiplexer, an inline box otherwise). troubleshoot is a deprecated alias.
.SH OPTIONS
This command takes no flags.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook assist
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook assist "why did this build fail?"
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
